description: This fuss-free beef taco salad is perfect for when you want something quick, easy and delicious. This tasty taco bowl is ready in less than 30 minutes.
name: Beef Taco Salad Recipe | Woolworths
recipeIngredient: 0.33 cup Woolworths extra virgin olive oil
1 baby cos lettuce, trimmed, finely shredded
100g Thomas Dux Vintage Cheddar, coarsely grated

recipeInstructions.text: Heat half of the oil in a large frying pan over medium heat. Cook half of the tortilla, turning, for 1 minute or until golden and crisp. Transfer to a paper towellined plate. Repeat with remaining oil and tortilla wedges.
Add mince to same pan over mediumhigh heat and cook, breaking up lumps with a wooden spoon, for 7 minutes or until browned. Add seasoning and cook for 1 minute or until fragrant.
Add undrained beans and cook, stirring, for 4 minutes or until liquid has almost evaporated.
Divide lettuce, tomato, cucumber, mince mixture, cheese and tortilla among bowls. Serve scattered with onion.
